Quickly and simply setting up git and npm from scratch, minimum viable solution
apt install git
apt install npm
apt install python
wget <git-credential-manager tar gz uri>
tar -xvf <path to tarball> -C /usr/local/bin
git-credential-manager configure
git config --global credential.credentialStore cache
git config --global user.name
git config --global user.email
git clone https://www.github.com/Alphaxius/LSCOM
cd to LSCOM/lscom
npm install

Blog post workflow instructions
put a temp file in LSCOM/lscom/src/blog/
python
import update_sitemap
update_sitemap("tempfile.txt")
exit python
mv tempfile.json to LSCOM/lscom/src/blog/ with intended name
rm temp text file in blog folder
update LSCOM/lscom/public/sitemap.xml with new name
update LSCOM/lscom/src/blog/blogIndex.json
update the default routes
add the newest route
update the previous route with the correct next link

Temp text file blog post format:
SOFTitle
Year
Date
Tags (space delimited)

Heading
Paragraph
Paragraph

#Heading (starts hidden with #)
Paragraph
ParagraphEOF
